<doc id="716977" wikidata="Q7633075" url="?curid=716977" title="Suckdog">
<text>Suckdog was an American underground band. The core members were the married couple Lisa Crystal Carver and Jean-Louis Costes. Suckdog toured the continental United States for several years with &quot;Suckdog Circus,&quot; performing a mix of wrestling, musical performances, film screenings, and general audience agitation. The heart of the Suckdog Circus were the noise music &quot;operas&quot; written by Costes and Carver which involved strange experimental fantasy stories with much blood and sex.

Other performers in the Suckdog Circus included Dame Darcy, Davey &quot;OHIO&quot; Highben, Coz the Shroom, Nick Zedd and Helen Suckpuppy.

A DVD was released in 2005 by Nut Music entitled &quot;Drugs Are Nice: A Suckumentary 1988-2005&quot;, containing excerpts of various performances, music videos, short films, and commentary from Lisa Crystal Carver and friends.

==Discography==
*&quot;Pears &amp; Plums&quot; (self-released, 1987)
*&quot;Rape GG&quot; with Costes (Costes Disques, 1988)
*&quot;Drugs are Nice&quot; (Suckdog, 1989)
*&quot;Little Flowers Dying&quot; (Suckdog, 1990)
*&quot;Onward Suckdog Soldiers&quot; (Suckdog, 1998)

